# General Project Conventions

- **Naming Conventions:**  
  - Use kebab-case for file and folder names  
  - Use PascalCase for React/Next.js components  
  - Use camelCase for variables and functions  
- **Indentation:**  
  - Use 2 spaces for indentation (or 4 if your team prefers)  
- **Imports:**  
  - Group imports by origin (external, internal, local)  
  - Use absolute imports for internal modules when possible  
- **Comments:**  
  - Write clear, concise comments for non-obvious logic  
  - Use JSDoc for public APIs and complex functions  
- **File Structure:**  
  - Keep related files in the same directory  
  - Avoid deep nesting of folders  
- **Commit Messages:**  
  - Write clear, concise commit messages  
  - Reference issue numbers when applicable  
- **Testing:**  
  - Write unit tests for critical logic  
  - Use descriptive test names  
- **Documentation:**  
  - Document public interfaces and modules  
  - Keep READMEs up to date  
- **Security:**  
  - Never commit sensitive data (API keys, passwords)  
  - Use environment variables for configuration  
